        <updateDate>2021-09-22T16:06:27Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Public Transit Safety Improvement Act of 2021 </strong></p> <p>This bill modifies requirements for approval of a public transportation agency safety plan to include a requirement that a safety committee approve the plan and any updates to the plan. The committee must consist of an equal number of frontline employee representatives (selected by the labor organization representing the plurality of the frontline workforce employed by the public transportation agency) and employer or state representatives.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
